				<title>(no title)</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-617078/scp-1513#post-2692142</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Tue, 15 Nov 2016 18:49:21 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>Soultear</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>1808168</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>There's something <em>missing</em> here. Linking articles is something frowned upon now, but I can forgive this skip because of its age, what I cannot and will not forgive are the gaping holes in research put on this display in the scip: The foundation finds out that these &quot;plants&quot; are capable of killing and dangerous in certain circumstances and doesn't even try to test them? That seems lazy and un-foundationlike. The idea is really interesting but those holes are untollerable.</p> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
